						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Parakēsarivarman, 4th year = c. A.D. 950.</p>						

						<p>Gift of 96 sheep for a lamp to the temple of Paramasvāmi at Tirumaṇañjēri, by a woman-servant <hi rend="italic">(peṇḍāṭṭi)</hi> attached to the (royal) kitchen at Tañjāvūr. She also presented a lamp-stand and the stone on which this inscription is engraved.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIX, No. 93.]</p>						

						</summary>
